node.text:
Look, if you have an exotic car and you get into a MINOR accident, you don’t want that accident to show up on the CARFAX because your vehicle could decrease in value by 15-20%. That’s a lot for a a minor scratch or dent.

If there are NO injuries and LITTLE to NO damage, you can resolve your claim without calling the police.

I get this question a lot. 

Most people assume that because they were in an accident, their rates will automatically go up. 

It all depends on the type of claim that you make with your insurance company and whether or not you were at fault for the accident.

node.text:
In the last month I’ve:

- Started advertising on 2 different radio stations
- Committed to tripling my content output
- Increased my ad spend by an additional six figures monthly
- Secured the venue to the number one legal summit in the world (and presold 32% of the tickets just from Instagram)
- Quadrupled the amount of paid 1:1 consultations for my coaching program
- Created an incentive/bonus structure for my law firm employees which will result in $250k in bonuses by the end of the year

And here are the results. 

Sometimes all you need to do is increase the ACTIVITY of what you’re already doing. 

One more rep at the gym. 

One more sales call. 

One more interview. 

One more client. 

One more email.

Just.

One.

More.

Simply put: a 1% improvement every single day will result in over 3700% improvement in just one year. 

That’s the power of consistency.

If there are NO injuries and LITTLE to NO damage, you can resolve your claim without calling the police.
